# Copy to `.env` and adjust. For `npm run dev`, prefer empty `VITE_API_BASE_URL` so requests stay on the Vite dev server and proxy to the local API.
# Public order tracking uses: GET /api/v1/public/order-tracking/:ownerCode/:orderId?token=... (same-origin + proxy in dev).

# Empty = same-origin + Vite proxy (see vite.config.ts). The proxy target defaults to `PORT` from `apps/api/.env` (or 4000) unless you set:
VITE_API_BASE_URL=
VITE_API_URL=
# VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET=http://127.0.0.1:4000
VITE_SOCKET_URL=
VITE_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your_google_maps_api_key_here

# --- Production / remote API (build with env in CI or use .env.production) ---
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://your-api.example.com
# VITE_API_URL=https://your-api.example.com
# VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET=https://your-api.example.com
